ice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hyndburnbc.gov.uk/borough-council-elections-2020/ |title=Hyndburn Borough Council - elections 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020 |work=The Hyndburn Borough Council}}</ref>. Approximately one third of the local council's 35 seats would have fallen up for election on that day<ref name=\"TEC-Notice\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/who-we-are-and-what-we-do/elections-and-referendums |title=Elections & Referendums - what we do |accessdate=March 7, 2020 |work=The Electoral Commission}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, on the same day, the election<ref name=\"PCC-Election\">{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_England_and_Wales_police,_fire_and_crime_commissioner_elections/ |title=2020 England and Wales PCC elections |accessdate=March 7, 2020 }}</ref> for Police and Crime Commissioner for the Lancashire Constabulary area<ref name=\"2020-England-and-Wales-PCC-Election\">{{Cite web|url=https://whocanivotefor.co.uk/elections/pcc.lancashire.2020-05-07/police-and-crime-commissioner-for-lancashire-constabulary/ |title=Who Can I Vote For - Lancs. P.C.C. Election |accessdate=March 7, 2020 }}</ref> would also have been held on Thursday 7 May 2020.\n\nUPDATE # On Friday, March 13th, the UK Government announced that ALL May-elections<ref name=\"MAY-Elections-Cancelled\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51876269/ |title=BBC - Coronavirus: English local elections postponed for a year |work=BBC News |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=March 13, 2020 }}</ref> will be postponed for a year, in response to the ongoing Coronavirus: outbreak.\n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Background==\nBefore the (Postponed) election [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] had a majority of 26 councillors, [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] had 9 councillors<ref name=\"HBC-Councillors\">{{Cite web|url=https://democracy.hyndburnbc.gov.uk/mgMemberIndex.aspx?FN=PARTY&VW=LIST&PIC=0 |title=Hyndburn Borough Council - Your councillors by political party 