ng|first=C.P.|year=2008|title=Mathematical analysis of Soros's theory of reflexivity|eprint=0901.4447|class=q-fin.GN}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Inside American Philanthropy: The Dramas of Donorship|last=Nielsen|first=Waldemar A.| year= 1996| publisher= University of Oklahoma Press|location=Norman, Oklahoma|isbn=978-0-8061-2802-3|pages=77\u201382}}\n* {{Cite book|title=The Volatility Machine: Emerging Economies and the Threat of Financial Collapse| last= Pettis| first= Michael| year=2001|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|isbn=978-0-19-514330-0}}\n* {{Cite journal|last=Stone|first=Diane|year=2007|title=Market Principles, Philanthropic Ideals and Public Service Values: The Public Policy Program at the Central European University|journal=PS: Political Science and Politics|volume=40|issue=3| pages= 545\u2013551|doi=10.1017/S1049096507070795|url=http://wrap.warwick.ac.uk/647/1/WRAP_Stone_Market_Principles.pdf}}\n*  {{cite journal| first= Diane| last= Stone| title= Transnational Philanthropy or Policy Transfer? The Transnational Norms of the Open Society Institute| journal= Policy and Politics| volume= 38| number= 2| year= 2010| pages= 269\u201387| doi=10.1332/030557309x458416| url= http://wrap.warwick.ac.uk/1741/1/WRAP_Stone_OSI__Policy_Transfer_FINAL.pdf}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q12908|n=no|c=Category:George Soros|b=no|v=no|voy=no|wikt=no|s=no|m=no|mw=no|species=no}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://www.soros.org/ Open Society Foundations]\n* [http://ineteconomics.org Institute for New Economic Thinking]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110511141012/http://www.project-syndicate.org/contributor/27 Column archives] at [[Project Syndicate]]\n* [http://www.nybooks.com/authors/157 Column archives] at ''[[The New York Review of Books]]''\n* {{C-SPAN|georgesoros}}\n* {{Charlie Rose view|242}}\n* {{Guardian topic}}\n* {{New York Times topic|people/s/george_soros}}\n* [https://www.forbes.com/profile/george-soros/ Forbes.com: George Soros]\n* [https: