ry=\n*The Wallflowers performs \"[[(Breach)|Sleepwalker]]\" and \"Hand Me Down\".\n*[[Baha Men]] makes a surprise appearance and performs \"[[Who Let the Dogs Out?]]\".\n*[[Robert De Niro]] appears as himself during Weekend Update to discuss Jimmy Fallon's negative review of ''[[Meet the Parents]]'' from the previous episode.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=489\n|EpisodeNumber2=4\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2000|11|4}}\n|RTitle=[[Charlize Theron]]\n|Aux1=[[Paul Simon]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Paul Simon performs \"Hurricane Eye\" and \"Old\".\n*SNL writer and stand up Hugh Fink appears as himself on Weekend Update in a commentary on [[Judaism]] and [[Joe Lieberman]].\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=490\n|EpisodeNumber2=5\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2000|11|11}}\n|RTitle=[[Calista Flockhart]]\n|Aux1=[[Ricky Martin]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Ricky Martin performs \"[[She Bangs]]\" and \"[[Loaded (Ricky Martin song)|Loaded]]\".\n*Chris Kattan impersonates Ricky Martin right before the real Ricky Martin performs the song \"Loaded\" (from Martin's album ''[[Sound Loaded]]'').\n*[[Giovanni Hidalgo]] performs percussion during Ricky Martin's musical performances. \n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=491\n|EpisodeNumber2=6\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2000|11|18}}\n|RTitle=[[Tom Green]]\n|Aux1=[[David Gray (musician)|David Gray]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*David Gray performs \"[[Babylon (David Gray song)|Babylon]]\" and appears in the \"Wedding\" sketch.\n*[[Drew Barrymore]] is in the audience and mentioned in the monologue by Tom Green.\n*[[Gwyneth Paltrow]] appears on Weekend Update.\n*Tom's parents Mary Jane Green and Richard Green appear in the opening monologue and the \"Wedding\" sketch.\n*Shawn Greenson, [[Derek Harvie]], and Glenn Humplik appear in the \"Wedding\" sketch.\n*Tom Green brought in his own writers for this episode, which didn't please the cast.<ref>{{cite book|title=Live From New York, The Uncensored History of Saturday Night Live}}</ref>\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=492\n|EpisodeNumber2=7\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2000|12|9}}\n|RTitle=[[Val Kilmer]]\n|Aux1=[[U2]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*U2 performs \"[[Beautiful Day]]\" and \"[[Elevation (song)|Elevation]]\".\n*The previous day marked the 20th anniversary of [[Death of John Lennon|John Lennon's assassination]]; [[Bono]] paid tribute to Lennon by singing a verse of \"[[All You Need Is Love]]\" over the end of \"Beautiful Day\".\n*The Director, Associate Directors, and Stage Managers who worked on this episode won a Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directorial Achievement.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=493\n|EpisodeNumber2=8\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2000|12|16}}\n|RTitle=[[Lucy Liu]]\n|Aux1=[[Jay-Z]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Jay-Z performs \"[[I Just Wanna Love U (Give It 2 Me)]]\" and \"Is That Your Chick,\" and cameos in the \"Robert Goulet Rap Album\" sketch.\n*[[Beanie Sigel]] and [[Memphis Bleek]] join Jay-Z for both musical performances and also appear in the \"Robert Goulet Rap Album\" sketch.\n\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=494\n|EpisodeNumber2=9\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|1|13}}\n|RTitle=[[Charlie Sheen]]\n|Aux1=[[Nelly Furtado]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Nelly Furtado performs \"[[I'm Like a Bird]]\".\n*Charlie Sheen reprises his role as Ricky Vaughn from the ''[[Major League (film)|Major League]]'' films in \"The NFL Pregame\" sketch.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=495\n|EpisodeNumber2=10\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|1|20}}\n|RTitle=[[Mena Suvari]]\n|Aux1=[[Lenny Kravitz]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Lenny Kravitz performs \"[[Again (Lenny Kravitz song)|Again]]\" and \"[[Mr. Cab Driver]],\" and appears in two live sketches as himself; one as holding auditions for Kyle and Sean DeMarco (Chris Kattan and Chris Parnell) and another going through airport security.\n*Former U.S. Attorney General [[Janet Reno]] makes a special appearance in the \"Janet Reno's Dance Party\" sketch where she confronts Janet Reno (portrayed by Will Ferrell).\n*[[Fred Wesley]] performs with the SNL Band.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=496\n|EpisodeNumber2=11\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|2|10}}\n|RTitle=[[Jennifer Lopez]]\n|Aux1=Jennifer Lopez\n|ShortSummary=\n*Jennifer Lopez performs \"[[Play (Jennifer Lopez song)|Play]]\" and \"[[Love Don't Cost a Thing (song)|Love Don't Cost a Thing]]\".\n*[[Tom Hanks]] makes a brief appearance during Weekend Update.\n*This episode was delayed by 45 minutes due to a double overtime [[XFL (2001)|XFL]] football game.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Carter|first1=Bill|title=XFL Game Intrusion on 'Saturday Night Live' Roils NBC Executives|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/02/13/business/xfl-game-intrusion-on-saturday-night-live-roils-nbc-executives.html|website=The New York Times|accessdate=3 February 2017|date=13 February 2001}}</ref>\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=497\n|EpisodeNumber2=12\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|2|17}}\n|RTitle=[[Sean Hayes (actor)|Sean Hayes]]\n|Aux1=[[Shaggy (artist)|Shaggy]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Shaggy performs \"[[It Wasn't Me]]\" with [[Rikrok]] and \"[[Angel (Shaggy song)|Angel]]\" with Rikrok and [[Rayvon]].\n*[[G. E. Smith]] and [[T-Bone Wolk]] perform with the Saturday Night Live Band.\n*[[Molly Shannon]]'s final episode as a cast member.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=498\n|EpisodeNumber2=13\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|2|24}}\n|RTitle=[[Katie Holmes]]\n|Aux1=[[Dave Matthews Band]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Dave Matthews Band performs \"[[I Did It (Dave Matthews Band song)|I Did It]]\" and \"[[The Space Between]]\".\n*[[Junior Brown]] performs with the Saturday Night Live Band.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=499\n|EpisodeNumber2=14\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|3|10}}\n|RTitle=[[Conan O'Brien]]\n|Aux1=[[Don Henley]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Don Henley performs \"[[Everything Is Different Now]]\" and \"[[The Heart of the Matter (song)|The Heart of the Matter]]\".\n*[[Max Weinberg]], the drummer on ''[[Late Night with Conan O'Brien]]'', and Weinberg's wife Becky appear in O'Brien's opening monologue.\n*[[Ben Affleck]] appears at the end of the \"Boston Teens at the Liquor Store\" sketch.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=500\n|EpisodeNumber2=15\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|3|17}}\n|RTitle=[[Julia Stiles]]\n|Aux1=[[Aerosmith]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Aerosmith performs \"[[Jaded (Aerosmith song)|Jaded]]\" and \"[[Big Ten Inch Record]]\".\n*[[David Copperfield (illusionist)|David Copperfield]] appears during \"Weekend Update\".\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=501\n|EpisodeNumber2=16\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|4|7}}\n|RTitle=[[Alec Baldwin]]\n|Aux1=[[Coldplay]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Coldplay performs \"[[Yellow (Coldplay song)|Yellow]]\" and \"[[Don't Panic (Coldplay song)|Don't Panic]]\".\n*[[David Spade]] appears on Weekend Update to plug his movie ''[[Joe Dirt]]''. Co-star [[Kid Rock]] also makes an appearance and does a few \"Hollywood Minute\" jokes.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=502\n|EpisodeNumber2=17\n|Origi