irst performance. Eve performs \"[[Who's That Girl? (Eve song)|Who's That Girl?]]\" for the second performance.\n*[[Molly Shannon]] makes an appearance in the \"Doctor's Office\" sketch.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=503\n|EpisodeNumber2=18\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|5|5}}\n|RTitle=[[Pierce Brosnan]]\n|Aux1=[[Destiny's Child]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Destiny's Child performs \"[[Survivor (Destiny's Child song)|Survivor]]\" and \"[[Emotion (Samantha Sang song)|Emotion]],\" and also appears in a sketch as former members of \"Gemini's Twin\", a recurring parody of the group.\n*[[Julia Stiles]] appears in the cold opening, as George W. Bush's daughter, [[Jenna Bush|Jenna]].\n*[[Molly Shannon]] appears in an SNL Digital Short, \"Five Finger Di$count\".\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=504\n|EpisodeNumber2=19\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|5|12}}\n|RTitle=[[Lara Flynn Boyle]]\n|Aux1=[[Bon Jovi]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Bon Jovi performs \"[[It's My Life (Bon Jovi song)|It's My Life]]\" and \"[[You Give Love a Bad Name (song)|You Give Love a Bad Name]]\". He and [[Richie Sambora]] also appear in a skit holding auditions for backup dancers with Kyle and Sean DeMarco (Chris Kattan and Chris Parnell). \n*[[Lou Reed]] makes an appearance on Weekend Update.\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|EpisodeNumber=505\n|EpisodeNumber2=20\n|OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|2001|5|19}}\n|RTitle=[[Christopher Walken]]\n|Aux1=[[Weezer]]\n|ShortSummary=\n*Weezer performs \"[[Hash Pipe]]\" and \"[[Island in the Sun (Weezer song)|Island in the Sun]]\".\n*Former cast member [[Kevin Nealon]] appears during Weekend Update to tell viewers he is not on ''SNL'' anymore and that viewers who do see him are watching reruns from the 1990s that at the time aired on [[Comedy Central]].\n*[[Winona Ryder]] appears during The Weekend Update Cliffhanger.\n*[[Jerry Minor]]'s final episode as a cast member.\n*[[Chris Parnell]]'s final episode as a cast member (until the middle of the [[Saturday Night Live (season 27)|next season]]).\n|LineColor=235454\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Specials==\n{{#invoke:Episode table|main\n|background=#235454\n|title=\n|airdate=\n|episodes=\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|LineColor=235454\n|Title=2000 Presidential Bash\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2000|11|3}}\n|ShortSummary=The special included election material from this year and years past. Rachel Dratch, Will Ferrell and Darrell Hammond hosted the special while doing a number of different impressions. This special also featured cameo appearances from George W. Bush, Al Gore, [[Jesse Ventura]], [[George H.W. Bush]], [[Barbara Bush]] and [[Dana Carvey]].\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|LineColor=235454\n|Title=Thursday Night Live (1) \n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|2|1}}\n|ShortSummary=\"The Culps' Mandatory Drug Awareness Assembly\" sketch from this episode was included in the prime-time special \"SNL Mother's Day Special 2001\" as well as the clip show \"The Best of Will Ferrell\".\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|LineColor=235454\n|Title=Thursday Night Live (2) \n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|2|8}}\n|ShortSummary=\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|LineColor=235454\n|Title=The Best of Molly Shannon \n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|3|20}}\n|ShortSummary=The special included material featuring Molly Shannon during her stint on the show. Sketches include \"Mary Katherine Gallagher,\" \"Leg Up,\" \"The Courtney Love Show,\" \"Pretty Living,\" \"Delicious Dish,\" \"Rockettes Auditions,\" \"Monica Lewinsky in Congress,\" \"Fanatic\" (film), \"Blind Date At The Airport,\" \"Veronica and Co.,\" \"Dame Elizabeth Taylor,\" and \"Jeannie Darcy\".\n}}\n\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Saturday Night Live (season 26)\n|LineColor=235454\n|Title=Mother's Day Special 2001 \n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2001|5|13}}\n|ShortSummary=The first SNL Mother's Day special since 1993, the episode featured the cast and their mothers talking about their favorite sketches aired on the show. Sketches included \"Behind the Music: Rock & Roll Heaven\", \"TRL: Gemini's Twin\", \"Mango vs. J.Lo\", \"The Weakest Link\" and more. This special contained a special tribute to singer-songwriter [[Minnie Riperton]], who was the mother of cast member Maya Rudolph.\n}}\n}}\n\n==''The Ladies Man'' film==\n{{main|The Ladies Man (2000 film)}}\nBased on [[Leon Phelps]]' popular sketches, ''[[The Ladies Man (2000 film)|The Ladies Man]]'' film was released on October 13, 2000. The film's star [[Tim Meadows]] left Saturday Night Live at the end of the previous season but returned to promote the film in the first episode of this season. Cast members [[Will Ferrell]] and [[Chris Parnell]] and former [[Saturday Night Live|SNL]] cast member [[Mark McKinney]] co-starred in this film. The movie was panned by critics and flopped at the box office.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[History of Saturday Night Live (2000\u20132005)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Saturday Night Live}}\n\n[[Category:Saturday Night Live seasons|26]]\n[[Category:Saturday Night Live in the 2000s]]\n[[Category:2000 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:2001 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:Television programs directed by Beth McCarthy-Miller]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toNational Anthem (disambiguation)(link changed toThe National Anthem (Radiohead song)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saturday_Night_Live_(season_26)"}
